Starting at 10 million worker bots, panel lifetime increases by 10%. This increases by 10% each time you multiply your workers by 10.

lifetime *= 1 + 0.1 * log10(Workers / 1e6)

Counting sheep is such a breeze, Helps me fall asleep with ease, One by one they jump the fence, Takes me to dreamland in suspense.
White and fluffy, soft and neat, Lead me to slumber so sweet, Close my eyes, take a deep breath, Counting sheep, I meet my rest.
Over the hills and far away, Sheep are counting every day, A bedtime ritual, tried and true, Helping me and maybe you.

The more maintenance efforts, the longer the panels will last and function effectively. This process extends the life of panels and ensures optimal performance, reducing the risk of failures and improving system reliability.

skillDescription: So, planets are made out of matter, right? Well, so are Assembly Lines! Getting enough assembly lines together should create more planets. Don't ask why robots don't do the same.
skillTechnicalDescription: Gain <color=#A3FFFE>Planets</color> equal to <color=#91DD8F>log10(<color=#A3FFFE>Assembly Lines</color>)</color>.

skillDescription: Have you heard of matrioshka worlds? Basically worlds layered into worlds layered into worlds. This technique, other than extremely space efficient, allows planets to give birth to more planets based on how many planets exist.
skillTechnicalDescription: Gain <color=#A3FFFE>Planets</color> based on <color=#91DD8F>log2(<color=#A3FFFE>Planets</color>)</color>.

skillDescription: Stuff happens, and your production layout is prepared for everything and anything. This allows for a flexible production boost, boosting the highest and the lowest layer of the dyson swarm.
skillTechnicalDescription: You now produce <color=#A3FFFE>50%</color> more <color=#A3FFFE>Assembly Lines</color>. Additionally, after <color=#A3FFFE>100 Planets</color>, <color=#A3FFFE>Planets</color> production boosted by <color=#A3FFFE>50%</color>

skillDescription: Death, life, death, life. An eternal loop of what will come to pass. Being prepared not only helps your psychology, but also your pocket dimensions.
skillTechnicalDescription: Every bought <color=#A3FFFE>Data Center</color> gives a <color=#A3FFFE>1%</color> boost to production of <color=#A3FFFE>Data Centers</color>.

skillDescription: You noticed a significant efficiency potential. By introducing tiny condensed spheres (nicknamed bubbles) of solar energy, your panels in the pocket dimensions have something to do, resulting in a significant boost to production.
skillTechnicalDescription: <color=#A3FFFE>Pocket Dimensions</color> gain <color=#A3FFFE>1%</color> production boost for every <color=#A3FFFE>second </color>of <color=#A3FFFE>Panel Lifetime</color>.

skillDescription: It was only a matter of time before your most trusted workers entered your pocket dimensions. The results are quite astonishing, be it they take time to be noticeable.
skillTechnicalDescription: Over the course of an hour, <color=#A3FFFE>Pocket Dimensions</color> gain a production boost with the cap of <color=#A3FFFE>100x</color>.

skillDescription: 'Fancy name for a fancy boost. You always excelled in geometry, time to apply the knowledge to your dyson swarm empire. '
skillTechnicalDescription: <color=#A3FFFE>Data Centers</color> gain a 10% production for every <color=#91DD8F>log10(<color=#A3FFFE>Servers</color>)</color>.

skillDescription: Why spend multiple threads computing multiple things, when you can instead use all threads to compute all things, in a parallel fashion. Your Servers become much more efficient this way, boosting your Data Centers.
skillTechnicalDescription: <color=#A3FFFE>Data Centers</color> gain a 10% production for every <color=#91DD8F>log2(<color=#A3FFFE>Servers</color>)</color>.

skillDescription: Using the same old server line-up seriously dampers with your progress. By utilizing quantum mechanics, you can now have servers that are simultaneously on, off, and both, boosting their efficiency in ways you don't quite understand.
skillTechnicalDescription: Production of <color=#A3FFFE>Data Centers</color> from <color=#A3FFFE>Pocket Dimensions</color> is boosted by <color=#91DD8F>Log2(<color=#A3FFFE>Rudimentry Singularity Production</color>)</color>.

skillDescription: Lowering Suspicion allows... wait, wrong game.
skillTechnicalDescription: Get <color=#A3FFFE>10x</color> as many <color=#A3FFFE>Servers</color> from <color=#A3FFFE>Rudimentary Singularity</color>.

skillDescription: Go faster, innovate harder, and take some prisoners.
skillTechnicalDescription: <color=#A3FFFE>Servers</color>, <color=#A3FFFE>AI Managers</color>, and <color=#A3FFFE>Assembly Lines</color> are <color=#A3FFFE>3x</color> stronger. <color=#A3FFFE>Planets</color> and <color=#A3FFFE>Data Centers</color> are <color=#A3FFFE>3x</color> weaker.

skillDescription: Create dedicated server 'clusters' for your own benefit.
skillTechnicalDescription: For every <color=#91DD8F>log10(<color=#A3FFFE>Servers</color>)</color>, <color=#A3FFFE>Servers</color> are <color=#A3FFFE>5%</color> better, and <color=#A3FFFE>Server</color> Production from <color=#A3FFFE>Rudimentary Singularity</color> is <color=#A3FFFE>5%</color> stronger.
